421	5	29	HA solutions provide a fully automated failover to a backup system so that users and applications can continue working without disruption. HA solutions must be able to provide an immediate recovery point. At the same time, they must provide a recovery time capability that is better than the recovery time that you experience in a non-HA solution topology. 1.4 How to prepare for IT resiliency It can seem like a daunting challenge to create an always-on service, and there is no one technology that solves all problems. IT resiliency is a choice. So, what should be considered when tackling this problem? First, consider points of failure. Any component of your system that does not have a backup can lead either to reduced throughput, reduced processing power, or a service outage.	[-0.05211641,0.027884591,-0.003431005,-0.014245888,0.022649217,0.011192469,-0.0072167786,0.09054387,-0.080775306,-0.0154553065,-0.03413082,0.0782494,0.044979274,-0.050340366,0.020321088,-0.017151656,0.049245924,-0.0668421,-0.02706303,0.007986214,-0.06322241,0.007869061,-0.07641805,0.047458533,-0.02281475,0.049607635,0.012823154,-0.05705298,-0.039130718,-0.057147212,-0.02527172,-0.056498192,0.010822505,0.008717616,0.027123803,0.12327432,-0.025717936,-0.028613467,-0.013309487,-0.060267553,-0.0008219482,-0.027687363,-0.06625097,-0.0012112809,-0.06005259,-0.056435894,0.047701795,-0.0026541082,0.023289261,-0.013349405,0.04051877,0.017689705,0.049589746,0.017982457,-0.0321613,0.07528952,0.0030046427,-0.013048137,-0.028608322,-0.017678082,0.009222568,0.037422597,-0.003369044,-0.03862819,0.07259939,0.054792564,0.07191109,0.017028939,0.03004221,0.07395779,-0.080955915,0.049132798,-0.018701483,0.030245407,0.014363237,0.012812125,0.04023197,-0.045461424,0.010496549,0.09266507,0.06743404,0.022053836,-0.029894019,0.08757421,-0.023767628,0.020646807,-0.03341337,-0.028243532,0.012865352,-0.059568692,0.018636804,0.0765245,0.12416036,0.0045859637,0.08186873,0.00837053,0.026638163,-0.011641239,0.03377846,-