428	5	36	Copyright IBM Corp. 2024. 15 Chapter 2. Technical view on IBM LinuxONE resiliency This chapter explores IBM LinuxONE capabilities to help achieve the highest platform resiliency and availability. It describes the various aspects of a virtualized environment, including the IBM LinuxONE processor reliability, availability, and serviceability (RAS) characteristics; Processor Resource System Manager (PRSM) and Dynamic Partition Manager (DPM) operation modes; and virtualization and hypervisors, such as zVM and Kernel-based Virtual Machine (KVM). It also covers resiliency automation for the infrastructure; the LinuxONE InputOutput (IO) capabilities with Fibre Channel connection (IBM FICON) and Fibre Channel Protocol (FCP) SCSI; and networking through internal network capabilities and network cards. This chapter includes the following topics:  2.1, Layers of resiliency based on IBM LinuxONE on page 16  2.2, Infrastructure on page 16  2.3, Operating environments on page 25  2.4, LinuxONE virtual storage on page 35  2.5, LinuxONE Virtual Network on page 37  2.6, Applications on page 41  2.7, Management on page 45  2.8, Automation on page 47  2.9, Building the related deployment model on page 58 2	[-0.0543326,-0.013439448,-0.05371579,-0.043939058,0.0377309,0.0033209624,-0.012822838,0.11950157,-0.07751285,-0.03878319,0.016622301,0.116398625,0.022504486,-0.06531573,0.013382833,-0.006443587,0.09630614,-0.007931186,-0.036969107,-0.016819058,0.02404724,-0.06504694,-0.061844677,-0.06489098,0.055667456,-0.014664933,-0.033308007,0.027759446,-0.006959933,-0.0013194621,-0.029432267,0.032792535,-0.008650625,0.029593615,-0.021914592,0.06875523,0.109237134,-0.128901,-0.02341073,-0.06330346,-0.07755125,-0.06464896,-0.07992202,0.0018936364,0.038843233,0.036925666,0.03605874,-0.030009573,-0.040525634,-0.04905058,-0.032412022,-0.03112388,0.12231688,0.09744054,-0.017879082,-0.0033310936,-0.0053649438,0.009102248,-0.031673867,0.017552542,0.02355109,-0.020555383,0.0059779417,0.055555917