412	5	20	Copyright IBM Corp. 2024. ix Preface This IBM Redbooks publication describes the concepts of resiliency as they relate to information technology systems. This book focuses on a LinuxONE server as a foundation model. Understanding uptime helps you understand the importance of availability for a business, institution, or governmental agency. Authors This book was produced by a team of specialists from around the world working at IBM Redbooks, Poughkeepsie Center. Ewerson Palacio is an IBM Redbooks Project Leader. He holds a bachelors degree in Math and Computer Science. Ewerson worked for IBM Brazil for over 40 years and retired in 2017 as an IBM Distinguished Engineer. Ewerson has co-authored many IBM Z publications, and created and presented IBM Redbooks seminars worldwide. Brian Hugenbruch CISSP is a Senior Software Engineer with IBM Z and LinuxONE. Officially, he is the IBM zVM Cryptography and Security Development lead. He has also served as the LinuxONE Resiliency Technical Lead since 2020, and in this capacity he drove the platform to its Eight 9s calculation. He combines these two sides of his work in the topics of cyber resiliency and digital forensics. He writes and speaks on these topics in numerous forums and conferences. Wilhelm Mild is an IBM Executive IT Architect and Open Group Distinguished Architect. He designs IBM LinuxONE and IBM Z solution architectures that feature containerization, Red Hat OpenShift Container Platform, end-to-end security, resiliency, high availability and disaster recovery (HADR), and network topologies for complex application landscapes. He speaks at international customer events, and teaches classes and hands-on labs. Filipe Miranda is a principal technical specialist for the Red Hat Synergy team at IBM. He has 15 years of experience with open-source technologies. He is an author of several IBM Redbooks and technical articles. He is a member of the zAcceleration team. His key skills include IBM Cloud Paks, Red Hat OpenShift, DevOps, and other technologies that are part of the hybrid cloud portfolio. Anderson Augusto Silveira is a Senior Technical Specialist for LinuxONE, Linux on IBM Z, and Red Hat OpenShift within IBM. He has 12 years of experience in virtualization and open-source technologies. He works on mission-critical projects worldwide, trains teams of IBM Business Partners and Clients, and helps and supports the adoption of new technologies and products	[-0.07062664,0.008793972,-0.12506784,-0.04635556,0.005421145,-0.052678876,0.03387096,0.11641553,-0.0045165024,-0.04273424,-0.010878234,0.099480696,0.13828912,-0.033527117,-0.015044294,-0.012952981,0.008612626,-0.004281179,-0.07978237,-0.082191534,-0.022275763,-0.075357534,-0.037914693,-0.08350126,0.020135079,-0.015648538,0.00085826335,-0.01358663,-0.03450252,-0.030118693,-0.004983907,0.029403115,0.029207012,0.06531698,0.0077016493,0.07629175,0.13363348,-0.06160472,0.03780249,-0.09415533,-0.08183447,-0.016831957,-0.0668268,0.043830935,-0.008282328,0.010682267,0.05555298,-0.017979976,-0.10241581,-0.0691969,-0.046455592,-0.007456719,0.059563242,0.05927234,-0.032662205,0.036419537,0.029852804,0.017141392,-0.03580331,-0.04361555,0.014478585,-0.019984797,-0.03713627,0.048791472,-0.0084843375,0.066396885,0.068797365,-0.025200214,-0.01086872,0.005879358,-0.038318537,-0.02442443,-0.03375009,0.07892053,-0.053856246,-0.0009753052,0.0029470238,-0.02033393,0.04806122,-0.004540863,0.077372134,0.033629205,-0.023160623,0.0459889,-0.008430924,0.016894793,-0.038496606,0.031046083,0.05051801,0.034265585,0.062367793,0.06603157,0.08001866,0.029197404,-0.04243635,-0.029531319,0.04373377,-0.01676596,-0.042882625,0.066943794,-0.005598005,0.078412205,0.06930541,-0.071794234,-0.010824955,-0.014988158,0.076284714,0.04227015,-0.061710514,0.025379159,-0.03114329,-1.2496207e-06,-0.029262546,-0.06543227,0.0072553214,0.01857513,-0.15382151,0.05268731,-0.028279623,-0.030307395,0.0924147,0.041094333,-0.03366445,-0.048821542,0.011781714,0.0075196796,-0.0