415	5	23	Copyright IBM Corp. 2024. 1 Chapter 1. IT resiliency matters IT resiliency is about the entire IT infrastructure being consistently available, which includes services and data. Also, many organizations operate in highly regulated industries and must comply with strict IT resiliency standards. Service providers offer certain service levels pertaining to quality, availability, and responsiveness that they are obligated to meet. This chapter describes the concepts of resiliency as they relate to information technology systems. This book focuses on a LinuxONE server as a foundation model. Understanding uptime helps you understand the importance of high availability (HA), business continuity (BC), and disaster recovery (DR). This chapter includes the following topics:  1.1, The impact of downtime on page 2  1.2, IT resiliency is a journey on page 3  1.3, IT resiliency goes beyond disaster recovery on page 5  1.4, How to prepare for IT resiliency on page 6  1.5, Deployment models for IBM LinuxONE resiliency on page 9 1	[-0.032371577,-0.021366173,-0.026637904,-0.057437148,0.025104582,-0.019221291,0.0021195523,0.082135715,-0.012860624,-0.034573715,-0.03774713,0.14494915,0.07388049,-0.07156036,0.016256142,-0.05467957,0.041678756,-0.056817167,-0.08585824,-0.07821371,-0.0250791,-0.0026610617,-0.0931952,0.01153228,0.0063517983,-0.009877019,-0.029093634,-0.0031034497,-0.03986569,-0.037959196,-0.07576757,0.023537349,-0.02530958,0.009404596,0.025237733,0.108733125,0.092438236,-0.030592209,0.03665876,-0.02917161,-0.037435558,-0.04832676,-0.07459929,0.026489137,-0.00011669112,-0.029646311,0.00825858,-0.038620736,-0.034849085,-0.019129572,0.009951743,-0.020276645,0.079538345,0.011261792,-0.015986064,0.050683025,0.002671978,0.018953534,-0.05166037,-0.032178123,0.05951996,-0.024427393,-0.02977731,0.07087154,0.05691486,0.025529547,0.034028616,-0.013364171,-0.0074381894,-0.02241401,-0.05361963,-0.029843725,-0.015620986,0.06358488,-0.023314653,-0.004236958,0.054168582,0.03722209,