420	5	28	6 IBM LinuxONE Resiliency Continuous operations A CO environment enables nondisruptive backups and system maintenance that is coupled with CA of services. The goal of BC is to mitigate or mask the effect of planned outages from consumers. It employs nondisruptive hardware and software changes, nondisruptive configuration, and software coexistence. zVM Live Guest Relocation (LGR), for example, enables CO because workloads can be moved from one system to another system at will. Continuous availability CA is a combination of CO and HA. It is designed to deliver nondisruptive service to consumers 247. There is no impact from planned or unplanned outages. Red Hat OpenShift Container Platform is an example of a CA solution. It enables HA by removing SPOFs within the hardware and its software environment. It enables CO by enabling rolling system restarts, nondisruptive updates, and workload relocation to mask planned events. Disaster recovery DR is protection against unplanned outages through a reliable and predictable recovery process. Examples include the inability to access storage, or a site disaster. DR is the ability to respond to an interruption in services by implementing a DR plan to restore critical business functions. DR is more reactive than HA solutions. DR solutions typically enable recovery within 24 - 72 hours, and HA solutions enable recovery within 1 - 2 hours of an event. As with any event, the duration and scope of the event dictates when usage of the DR plan is necessary. A DR process might be an appropriate response, even with events that last less than the 24 - 72-hour standard. Business continuity BC is the ability of a business to withstand outages and operate important services normally and without interruption in accordance with SLAs. BC includes high availability and disaster recovery (HADR), and it can be defined as the ability to withstand all outages (planned, unplanned, and disasters) and provide continuous processing for all critical workloads. The goal is for the outage time to be less than 0.001 of total service time. A HA environment typically includes more demanding RTOs (seconds to minutes) and more demanding RPOs (zero user disruption) than a DR scenario. HA solutions provide a fully automated failover to a backup system so that users and applications can continue working without disruption. HA solutions must be able to provide an immediate recovery point. At the same time, they must provide a recovery time capability that is better	[-0.039199647,0.010626808,-0.04601089,0.0078457305,0.042611733,-0.006341163,-0.008937556,0.084359035,0.026449308,-0.022466509,0.020973636,0.071550615,0.041915555,-0.04234338,0.024733968,-0.058706854,0.05457509,-0.03479003,-0.09200954,0.012829422,-0.022670096,0.045287624,-0.1259567,0.02902278,-0.01566241,-0.008572312,-0.048713826,-0.000100463934,0.0051386496,-0.0445436,-0.019860284,0.047819674,-0.026647633,-0.03708224,0.01704698,0.13848504,-0.008555885,-0.04768981,-0.0753517,-0.06692791,-0.04159995,-0.02822765,-0.033311196,0.024155654,0.0045144586,-0.03520012,-0.021815393,-0.076708116,-0.050919574,-0.029808108,0.02230747,0.013724225,0.059862603,0.15102553,-0.011300351,0.06064154,0.016262468,-0.024845455,-0.02741831,-0.08455966,0.07821707,-0.0029154385,-0.010996057,0.021482848,0.03616108,0.0542935,0.033787366,-0.04606604,0.032350566,-0.025156876,-0.052770276,-0.034526154,0.028179694,0.019168844,0.043482557,-0.022402616,0.04397623,-0.036381487,0.07912521,0.053522505,0.09135807,0.06826287,-0.05267768,-0.004356338,-0.054901224,0.012168042,-0.014387366,0.026020316,0.011767386,-0.024012307,0.04228349,0.10368157,0.12926152,-0.04367596,-0.015327718,-0.04899616,0.023596533,-0.04117711,0.0492041,0.024859663,0.102154516,0.04791862,0.035213776,-0.049937304,-0.06012962,-0.059666466,0.007920272,-0.014237289,-0.016965443,0.0032970312,-0.024327857,-0.0015116173,0.030826513,-0.058866546,-0.037484158,0.06396796,-0.088140585,-0.021653334,0.031013893,-0.06957481,0.07183436,-0.00