422	5	30	8 IBM LinuxONE Resiliency Balancing the risks and costs of mitigation is essential to achieving business goals. By balancing the risk of a type of failure and the cost of a solution, you can determine how much redundancy and availability management you can design into your IT infrastructure. By understanding the real cost of service unavailability, you can calculate the costs that you can sustain to provide this availability. These factors also determine when you can do maintenance and upgrades to the IT infrastructure. As illustrated in Figure 1-1, you must evaluate the risk and impact of the outage and decide whether the design must be changed to meet the cost implications of service outages. Maybe these cost implications should be adjusted? Figure 1-1 Resiliency optimization Under-investment can result in spending money by not-spending money, increasing risks to the business. If an outage occurs, you might be able to bear the cost of recovery at the time of the outage, but the cost of recovery can be greater than the cost of prevention. Over-investment can result in excess solution costs. By overspending on high levels of protection, you can incur expenses and risks that are associated with lost opportunity. 1.4.2 How IBM LinuxONE helps IBM LinuxONE has a sterling record of system uptime. The relative availability of the underlying server hardware, through a host of technical means that are described in Chapter 2, Technical view on IBM LinuxONE resiliency on page 15, can boost the uptime of applications by virtue of the system on which it is running. This is not to say that one server is enough, or that LinuxONE hardware solves all problems. Again, system resiliency is a lifestyle choice, and this means that every SPOF in storage, compute, networking, virtual infrastructure, physical site maintenance, and others must be addressed as part of an overall resiliency and DR plan. Optimum resilience risk balance Resilience optimization Low Level of resilience Costs from risk events Low Costs of mitigation solutions High High	[-0.045331284,0.021603653,0.01245689,-0.043463282,0.046473555,-0.009797525,0.03883341,0.13508858,-0.013507533,0.013707637,-0.021777362,0.07968586,0.08578031,-0.070399575,0.023503363,0.009203006,0.053125042,-0.024749259,-0.12457479,-0.04438883,0.024814926,-0.08066368,-0.07840764,-0.0008355334,-0.02481164,0.016665753,0.018579144,0.0033584635,-0.0070712343,-0.0136041315,-0.01905167,0.065756455,-0.03664873,-0.06266325,0.012310275,0.09398783,0.01963402,-0.010303595,0.030093642,0.00045192687,-0.06353788,-0.015514559,-0.06245074,0.019465547,-0.03055617,-0.059464484,-0.045462616,-0.046335485,0.004226611,-0.016421976,0.026254172,0.022911688,0.04441062,0.019598318,-0.042873275,-0.037002042,0.03779736,-0.022452245,-0.075279646,-0.0053018066,0.049652427,-0.04237007,-0.0038375515,0.008058114,0.007496818,-0.016568944,0.056541227,0.018512802,-0.040922105,0.106319144,-0.009736987,-0.047017887,-0.028781863,-0.02713933,-0.02478512,0.060123086,0.07422325,-0.015759632,0.046555016,0.033916872,0.09563545,0.0722304,-0.0067703216,0.03668788,-0.01618561,-0.018914571,-0.013671563,-0.025433961,0.07343409,-0.009629359,0.04467082,0.045871142,0.05770581,-0.009701418,0.05189299,0.04476458,-0.025810497,-0.033843227,-0.01583402,0.036251087,0.038540795,-0.014337061,0.11380274,-0.035121135,-0.0061357096,-0.06855588,-0.010752275,-0.036685318,0.0030860452,-0.0229259,0.030704325,-0.034226365,0.055678476,-0.006450859,0.026127165,0.054099623,-0.04896688,-0.024433725,0.022647332,-0.030645445,0.053547703,0.0073122736,0.036524665,-0.05917209,-0.040375546,0.036920868,-0.013583691,4.121054e-33,-0.05089321,0.013520899,-0.050262056,-0.06635668,-0.012623542,-0.096953824,-0.0064804857,0.014130201,-0.03370139,-0.016618442,0.0048434525,0.010982834,-0.01406542,-0.09252025,0.08933474,-0.0365269,0.026840046,0.08948356,0.13045104,-0.019442603,0.022266725,-0.14355248,0.025686089,-0.02590429,0.1043577,-0.08144176,0.051582664,-0.069145754,-0.03768302,0.0121