432	5	40	20 IBM LinuxONE Resiliency  Integrated Firmware Processor (IFP): Two cores are dedicated to supporting native PCIe features (for example, Remote Direct Memory Access over Converged Ethernet (RoCE) Express, zEDC Express, zHyperLink Express, and Coupling Express), and other firmware functions.  Central processor (CP): In LinuxONE, a CP may be exclusively used by a GDPS Virtual Appliance, which is a fully integrated software solution to provide continuous availability and disaster recovery (CADR) protection and failover automation of workloads on LinuxONE. For more information, see GDPS Virtual Appliance on page 53. In the unlikely event of a permanent core failure, each core can be individually replaced by one of the available spares. Core sparing is transparent to the OS and applications. The resiliency capabilities for the PUs include the following ones:  Transparent core sparing  Concurrent processor drawer repairadd, which includes processorcache chips, memory, and other internal components  Transparent SAP sparing System clocking LinuxONE has two OSCs for system clocking purposes: one primary and one secondary. If the primary OSC fails, the secondary detects the failure, takes over transparently, and continues to provide the clock signal to the system. Power The resiliency capabilities for power for LinuxONE include transparent failover and concurrent repair of all power parts and redundant AC inputs. The power supplies for LinuxONE are also based on the N1 design. The additional power supply can maintain operations and avoid an unplanned outage of the system. Cooling LinuxONE provides an N1 cooling function for the radiator-based and air-cooled model, which suits the needs of typical business computing. The N1 (redundant) cooling function for the fluid-cooled model suits the needs of enterprise computing. The resiliency capabilities for cooling include transparent failover and concurrent repair of cooling pumps, blowers, fans, and other items. The single-frame models do not have radiators. The cooling is accomplished by air that is forced by redundant fans. System control structure The system control structure includes redundant sideband control access to all units in the platform, and redundant network switches. The Support Elements (SEs) are connected to support processors in the CPC drawer, IO drawers, power supplies, and cooling units, where Hardware Management Appliances (HMAs) run. The HMA and SE are appliances that provide hardware management for IBM LinuxONE servers. Hardware platform management covers	[-0.07796719,0.001576535,-0.025931569,-0.042155568,0.09590711,0.0091366945,-0.026691774,0.097029924,0.0032154818,-0.027624112,0.028393527,0.032077376,0.0152796665,-0.053536832,0.026106035,-0.04502275,0.07386748,-0.018894767,0.008640997,0.0003189961,0.017088434,-0.020781254,-0.11878294,-0.027767455,0.025271636,-0.018437145,0.00839007,-0.0026671789,-0.032428727,-0.014467746,-0.02030582,-0.03581084,-0.031496536,0.068189226,0.022465525,0.018588893,0.07758578,-0.07286675,-0.015606972,-0.09992661,-0.07148964,-0.005478484,-0.09976405,0.041573912,0.013774891,0.03700354,0.0075918613,-0.032527808,-0.0481522,-0.035896584,0.021514654,-0.008122778,0.07776708,0.067546114,0.007299932,0.03880539,-0.024786256,0.0006686831,-0.030441722,0.039824713,0.0248966,-0.059251197,-0.00014263109,0.025175577,0.056222785,-0.015554285,0.10450267,-0.016480852,0.004623977,-0.0394302,0.016941754,-0.08301309,-0.017418724,0.028088612,-0.049700174,0.040410556,-0.011244121,-0.091766864,0.03022136,-0.08338545,0.0031904501,0.11830599,0.035478912,-0.013195536,0.09527193,-0.0039814296,-0.006995231,0.072074965,-0.009029979,-0.04087749,0.05017293,0.06770504,0.06393297,-0.028474415,0.08355894,0.0080530355,-0.0016888267,0.011771834,-0.065068975,0.006418139,0.014394775,-0.008652354,0.073363386,0.012921968,-0.0019363584,-0.015648097,-0.030998623,0.015876489,-0.068610914,-0.03681202,-0.04228113,0.07102555,0.0035385126,-0.040996034,0.07507456,-0.013528243,-0