436	5	44	24 IBM LinuxONE Resiliency 2.2.3 Physical network attachment capabilities This section covers the following topics:  IBM Remote Direct Memory Access over Converged Ethernet Express  Open Systems Adapter  Standard Ethernet support  OSA operating modes  Open System Adapter Support Facility IBM Remote Direct Memory Access over Converged Ethernet Express RoCE cards are similar to Open Systems Adapter (OSA) cards. They can share their ports, but can also run different network protocols in addition to the traditional ETH protocol. RoCE Express cards use a communication mechanism that is called Shared Memory Communication (SMC), which enables two SMC-capable peers to communicate by using a memory buffer that is allocated by each peer for the partners use. There are two types of SMC:  Shared Memory Communications over Remote Direct Memory Access (SMC-R) SMC-R is a network capability that strengthens performance for sharing data and reducing data transmission network overhead. SMC-R provides application-transparent usage of this new RoCE feature, which reduces the network overhead and latency of data transfers, effectively offering the benefits of optimized network performance between two LinuxONE processors.  Shared Memory Communications-Direct Memory Access (SMC-D) SMC-D enables direct access to shared virtual memory by providing a highly optimized network interconnect for IBM LinuxONE intra-CPC communications by using Internal Shared Memory. For more information, see Internal Shared Memory. Internal Shared Memory Internal Shared Memory (ISM) provides adapter virtualization with high scalability that enables LPARs (or guest VMs) to logically share virtual memory. ISM enables SMC-D, and provides savings in physical resources with performance benefits. Open Systems Adapter The OSA is a network controller that you can install in a LinuxONE IO cage. The OSA-Express features integrate network interface hardware and support many networking transport protocols. Every OSA-Express feature provides capabilities in the following areas:  Standard Ethernet support  Operating modes  Connectivity options (bandwidth and data throughput)  RAS Effectively, the OSA integrates the control unit and device into the same hardware. It does so by placing it on a single card that directly connects to the CPC IO bus. Standard Ethernet support The following Ethernet standards are applicable for OSA-Express features (standard transmission schemes):  IEEE 802.3 and IEEE 802.1  Ethernet 2.0  Data Integrity Extensions (DIX) 2	[-0.030838143,-0.061172973,-0.06496615,0.014544566,0.06071061,0.045204453,-0.037777543,0.12294478,0.01268411,-0.0069905305,-0.0014194646,0.094462246,-0.022794077,-0.042438406,0.016283067,0.012278387,0.057186965,0.015639558,-0.01802024,0.008421382,0.038071662,-0.04815204,-0.02779539,-0.03747047,0.006571095,-0.014317296,-0.012568701,-0.015745625,0.00088436535,-0.028476452,0.05833164,0.015112971,-0.0077660233,0.050354064,-0.09093359,-0.005958698,0.0754562,-0.0945517,-0.042047866,-0.11739985,-0.072806224,0.012903774,-0.040084798,0.03897084,-0.03177885,0.04263648,-0.010916707,-0.022414582,-0.032369368,-0.047239404,-0.01694837,-0.02903523,-0.0125958985,0.05695037,0.014113003,0.016616255,-0.08025336,-0.031158036,0.007680162,0.053207938,-0.012766301,-0.05906611,0.039667938,0.05448475,-0.028741857,-0.049279068,0.07703078,0.05841083,0.018360214,-0.05829662,-0.02777211,-0.0368958,-0.03435784,0.022063736,-0.048581474,0.09937069,0.016871898,-0.011142822,-0.0026572316,-0.012929806,-0.011813024,0.09660605,-0.02261909,-0.043021943,0.046294127,0.0155627895,-0.04213335,0.011538474,-0.04223947,-0.046215065,0.036440834,0.10966286,-0.03790513,-0.038281206,-0.04473625,-0.05328453,-0.04888392,0.0047906213,-0.0754341,0.06612414,0.044814777,0.08812134,0.047556564,-0.011298315,-0.0045170705,-0.0058374535,0.022443665,-0.028902192,-0.067664325,0.04311926,-0.07156403,0.01362112,-0.08773652,-0.027910188,-0.025172852,0.044075683,-0.075371824,0.014332178,0.051967457