438	5	46	26 IBM LinuxONE Resiliency Partitioning control specifications are partly contained in the InputOutput Configuration Data Set (IOCDS) and are partly contained in a system profile. The IOCDS and profile both are in the SE. An IOCDS contains information to define the IO configuration to the processor channel subsystem and is created by a program called IOCP. A second layer of virtualization is in each LPAR and can be realized by implementing a hypervisor in the LPAR, which enables the virtualization of all hardware resources, and thousands of Linux guests, which can be run concurrently in a single LinuxONE system. The two hypervisors that can be installed in a LinuxONE LPAR are zVM, and KVM:  With zVM, you can have the premier IBM hypervisor that has matured over decades and has leveraged granular resource sharing and resource shifting between the virtualized Linux virtual guests that are controlled by zVM.  With KVM, you can enable on LinuxONE, which is a hypervisor that is developed by the Open Source Community, LinuxONE was adapted by Red Hat, SUSE, and Canonical. Platform virtualization Platform virtualization is a principal strength of IBM LinuxONE. It is embedded in the architecture and built into the hardware, firmware, and OSs. For decades, the IBM LinuxONE platforms have been designed based on the concept of partitioning resources (such as CPU, memory, storage, and network resources). So, each set of features can be used independently with its own operating environment. Every LinuxONE platform is highly virtualized, with the goal of maximizing utilization of computing resources while lowering the total number of resources and cost that are needed to run critical workloads and solutions. Virtualization can help secure and isolate application workloads and data within virtual servers and storage devices for replication and restoration. With this added resiliency, you have greater flexibility in maintaining a highly available infrastructure while performing planned maintenance and in configuring low-cost DR solutions. 2.3.2 IBM Processor Resource Systems Manager The hardware-level virtualization capability in IBM LinuxONE, PRSM, is a Type-1 hypervisor that runs directly on bare metal so that you can create multiple LPARs. PRSM is a highly reliable and secure firmware-encapsulated virtualization technology that enables multiple OSs to run on the same physical platform. Each OS runs in its own LPAR. PRSM is a technology that is used in IBM LinuxONE to	[-0.035850324,-0.028011044,-0.08567261,-0.059268676,0.04686617,-0.010555396,-0.050485548,0.09303161,-0.036918107,-0.040177464,-0.0045599276,0.034178093,0.0041165696,-0.06506766,-0.042518802,-0.009236332,0.06590905,0.041555777,-0.039329898,0.03588117,0.0898657,-0.035481717,-0.026572855,-0.07798395,0.025931263,0.02517886,-0.043984666,0.023313908,0.027829597,-0.015812378,0.032179855,0.06697764,-0.01685478,0.06405987,-0.07222507,0.057531882,0.03051477,-0.1262482,-0.05955491,-0.002341361,-0.036286198,-0.023644855,-0.08345717,0.036964193,0.008366587,0.085139,-0.02296885,-0.03085063,-0.045596886,-0.047204696,-6.468351e-06,-0.060364053,0.13286425,0.11740804,-0.027404591,-0.011091199,0.016735801,-0.015481756,-0.009358094,-0.017847424,-0.021863079,0.059520084,-0.033991206,0.02881579,0.020573333,-0.025946636,0.047166485,0.02974344,-0.012764245,-0.1451699,0.0016081417,-0.012905197,-0.008674031,0.024022566,-0.09048681,0.032791782,0.022889575,-0.0077697905,0.064277686,-0.044310246,0.061381254,0.13389328,-0.03343211,-0.016895786,0.018380096,-0.0032876816,-0.046127,0.0797399,0.035626803,-0.007914682,0.037365984,0.0667306,0.036640458,-0.012385357,0.057585344,0.022965228,0.004068547,-0.052848946,0.06790211,0.043808814,0.00899705,-0.023216747,0.03808285,0.025699664,-0.02195535,-0.0019753675,0.0068797134,0.03671603,-0.13292895,-0.03553854,-0.024177035,0.009572813,-0.010820427,-0.05375413,0.035312902,0.04096981,0.015993504,0.06542214,0.01427936,-0.055797093,-0.053822797,-0.06779238,0.01206