439	5	47	SM is a highly reliable and secure firmware-encapsulated virtualization technology that enables multiple OSs to run on the same physical platform. Each OS runs in its own LPAR. PRSM is a technology that is used in IBM LinuxONE to provide logical partitioning and resource management capabilities. PRSM enables a LinuxONE system to be divided into multiple LPARs, each running its own OS instance and set of applications with the highest isolation. PRSM logically partitions the platform across the various LPARs to share resources, such as processor units and IO (for networks and storage), which enables a high degree of virtualization and the highest isolation concurrently. The main goal of PRSM is to maximize the usage of system resources and improve overall system performance. It enables up to 85 LPARs to run concurrently on a single physical LinuxONE Emperor server and up to 40 LPARs on a single LinuxONE Rockhopper, enabling organizations to consolidate workloads while isolating them for resiliency and reducing hardware costs.	[-0.043593857,0.0069255354,-0.07800772,-0.07043824,0.064774044,-0.03069935,0.010476208,0.07915401,0.008506561,-0.0008916167,0.016921401,0.069327116,-0.01489985,-0.057435166,0.02450443,0.004616979,-0.0018422541,0.0051841764,0.004673547,0.031697072,-0.008319477,-0.09543404,-0.07802741,-0.034756724,-0.013731307,0.026964767,-0.040719677,0.02838519,-0.0053508263,-0.060207855,0.028495165,-0.024712842,-0.025177885,0.040693548,-0.022986153,0.042393498,-0.01974869,-0.11138383,-0.09816281,-0.050959848,0.012447063,0.011023263,-0.09453044,0.036556948,-0.028681172,0.027605198,-0.003679841,0.0028576236,-0.003668602,-0.04865683,-0.021321401,-0.07660901,0.07135999,0.07176152,-0.09272323,-0.037223037,0.029648561,0.0032263754,-0.021396609,-0.02075137,-0.020136975,0.0010813467,-0.061443828,0.029827088,0.027882488,0.002229905,0.08833287,0.006618562,0.020306427,-0.06949245,0.0018776027,0.026430989,0.0063123037,0.048264146,-0.047971305,0.04260423,8.698646e-05