445	5	53	34 IBM LinuxONE Resiliency 2.3.7 Container platforms IBM LinuxONE offers robust support for various container technologies and platforms, which enables the usage of cloud-native applications like Linux-based workloads, microservices, hybrid cloud deployments, and their associated ecosystems. The following configuration options are available:  Linux applications  Microservices architecture  Cloud-native applications  Hybrid cloud deployments  Container platforms  Parallel Access Volume  HyperPAV  ECKD with HyperPAV  Using system internal network capabilities Linux applications IBM LinuxONE facilitates the containerization of Linux-based applications through technologies such as Open Container Initiative (OCI) compliant containers. Containers provide a lightweight and isolated runtime environment, which helps ensure consistency and portability across different environments. The LinuxONE powerful hardware resources and scalability make it an optimal choice for running large-scale containerized workloads. Microservices architecture LinuxONE is highly suitable for deploying microservices-based architectures by using containers. By breaking down complex applications into smaller, decoupled services, developers can independently develop, deploy, and scale these services. Containers enable efficient resource utilization and rapid deployment, which makes LinuxONE an ideal platform for managing microservices workloads. Cloud-native applications IBM LinuxONE fully supports the development and deployment patterns of cloud-native applications. These applications are designed to harness the benefits of containerization, scalability, and elasticity. Leveraging technologies such as Kubernetes, IBM LinuxONE enables automated container orchestration, scaling, and load balancing, which provide a reliable and high-performance foundation for running cloud-native applications. Hybrid cloud deployments IBM LinuxONE facilitates the deployment of containerized workloads in hybrid cloud environments. Using solutions like Red Hat OpenShift Container Platform, which supports multiple hardware architectures like IBM LinuxONE, enables the management and deployment of containers across both on-premises LinuxONE systems and public cloud platforms. This approach enables users to leverage containerization advantages while maintaining a consistent and secure environment throughout their hybrid cloud infrastructure. Container platforms LinuxONE supports many container platforms that provide capabilities for managing containerized applications. An example is the Red Hat OpenShift Container Platform, which is available for various hardware architectures, which include IBM LinuxONE. Red Hat OpenShift Container Platform, built on Kubernetes, offers a comprehensive environment for developing, deploying, and managing containerized applications. It includes features like automated scaling, load balancing, and container lifecycle management.	[-0.0047316724,0.043088727,-0.004219407,-0.08077781,0.05236297,-0.0672566,-0.0535434,0.031214865,-0.0073857326,-0.019986128,-0.01664639,-0.003530025,0.0006705821,-0.056204464,0.02124884,-0.03663459,0.11449503,0.04915849,-0.033769485,0.025713587,-0.0104381,-0.006243611,-0.033446595,-0.0480096,-0.00782277,0.057431474,-0.055850726,0.017439308,0.0055304775,-0.035545528,0.057486903,0.005643416,-0.034809373,0.036644995,0.009790333,0.10457552,0.060932685,-0.102176785,-0.06078958,-0.051121127,-0.06233187,-0.11157316,-0.056935158,0.034366846,-0.0041106516,-0.023663854,-0.0041654822,-0.08126943,0.0037932692,-0.020620275,0.008618806,-0.110998005,0.06594479,0.09970022,-0.05454454,-0.016841969,-0.03546266,0.044608925,0.017971272,-0.003828959,0.0278217,0.01349954,0.043344166,0.073871695,-0.022249717,-0.016308956,0.031150986,-0.037788067,0.021707002,-0.06830924,0.033880066,0.0071682674,-0.0025681646,0.030310666,-0.078925006,0.035835497,0.011520566,-0.018556388,0.017473783,0.036195897,0.060311794,0.093594216,-0.061357517,-0.008980976,-0.09