456	5	64	46 IBM LinuxONE Resiliency Here are the products that are included with IBM Infrastructure Suite for zVM and Linux:  IBM Tivoli OMEGAMON XE for Messaging on zVM and Linux  IBM Spectrum Protect Extended Edition  IBM Operations Manager for zVM  IBM Backup and Restore Manager for zVM  IBM Tape Manager for zVM (optional)  IBM Cloud Infrastructure Center (optional) 2.7.2 KVM Hypervisor Management Various tools exist for managing KVMs efficiently:  Libvirt Libvirt is a toolkit that provides a consistent and stable API for managing various virtualization solutions, including KVM. It offers command-line utilities (virsh) and APIs for management. For more information, see KVM Management Tools.  Virt-manager Virt-manager is a desktop application for managing KVMs. It provides a GUI to create, view, modify, and manage VMs. For more information, see Good GUI for KVM.  Cockpit Web Console Cockpit is a web-based server management tool that includes support for managing KVMs. It offers a web interface for VM management. For more information, see Tecmint.  WebVirtMgr: WebVirtMgr is a web-based interface for managing KVMs. It provides a browser-accessible platform to create and control VMs. For more information, see Reddit. 2.7.3 Container management Container management automates the creation, deployment, and scaling of containers. It also facilitates the organization of containers. Container management enables systems to work more efficiently, especially when the number of containers becomes too large for the IT team to handle. With Container management, IT teams can keep their environment more secure, and developers can explore its flexibility to create and deploy new apps and services. Docker container management software and Kubernetes container management facilitate the orchestration, security, and networking tasks. Container management software systems are available as both open-source and proprietary commercial products. 2.7.4 Kubernetes Kubernetes is an open-source platform for managing containerized workloads and services that facilitates both declarative configuration and automation. Kubernetes is portable, extensible, and has a large and rapidly growing ecosystem. Kubernetes services, support, and tools are widely available. Here are some of the Kubernetes features:  Auto scaling  Storage orchestration  Self-healing  Multi-cloud and hybrid cloud support	[-0.021097086,-0.008221921,-0.061346527,-0.043240547,0.024615113,-0.009183632,-0.032457836,0.09614878,-0.049043246,0.0017415178,0.027687827,-0.03860692,0.0400386,-0.026231078,0.018744998,-0.016158676,0.054436043,0.0051211608,0.0059005707,-0.05933165,-0.028674588,0.046755,-0.0069810664,-0.062104203,-0.01145879,-0.0015901842,-0.02541446,0.07496547,0.029395044,-0.025932003,-0.021463715,0.025524648,-0.02337124,0.058694303,-0.05894752,0.0764054,0.04940776,-0.07208821,-0.101361535,-0.047564466,-0.045425512,-0.014906565,-0.11103441,-0.06829007,0.00911034,0.087505214,0.017127972,-0.086040415,-0.013839764,-0.045999866,-0.024202617,-0.086549096,0.10279503,0.10942158,-0.028666835,0.044929337,0.032020215,-0.013834194,-0.01820705,-0.06473483,-0.024056625,0.056104165,-0.027479162,0.044594128,-0.07927662,0.01236049,0.061974496,0.09400409,0.0045559322,-0.052277163,-0.017038895,-0.05545174,-0.04432392,0.021434072,-0.13619408,0.0336384,-0.019280214,-0.027960153,0.043861117,0.021721633,0.06522267,0.07521862,-0.060407083,0.101177536,-0.0030802707,0.044105753,-0.017704815,0.02345765,0.08069614,0.05472625,0.05228226,0.036988996,0.086351745,-0.055790316,-0.03752079,-0.01740947,0.068069294,-0.024701307,0.03163234,0.034717396,0.026643053,0.0045917137,0.041332394,-0.019935595,0.034004934,0.03143149,0.023045348,0.031110585,-0.031413592,0.0408399,-0.035824474,0.03781003,-0.033165246,-0.069930784,0.032230966,0.05671921,0.017524622,0.042585254,-0.010356207,0.0016142303,0.042065114,-0.008654644,0.0418245,0.0013927869,0.043546423,0.069142476,-0.041029193,8.2396886e-33,-0.02772857,0.016590208,-0.10021425,-