460	5	68	50 IBM LinuxONE Resiliency OpenSAF checkpoint APIs OpenSAF is a checkpoint service that provides mechanisms for checkpointing and restoring an application state. It provides a series of APIs to help applications register for checkpoints and to perform the restoration of applications.  Service Availability Forum (SAF): Creates the Service Availability Specifications.  OpenHPI: The Hardware Platform Interface (HPI) abstracts the differences between hardware implementations, which provide a uniform interface to the hardware features.  OpenAIS: The Application Interface Specification (AIS) specifies an interface that applications use to exchange information with the service availability middleware (Cluster Resource Management). Heartbeat The heartbeat of a node in a cluster is a signal that is sent between nodes to indicate that they are still alive and functioning properly. It is used to detect when a node fails and initiate failover procedures. Sometimes, the heartbeat is used to monitor the health of a node and initiate maintenance actions.  Uses messaging between nodes to make sure that they are alive and available.  Determines whether an action is required when the heartbeat stops after a certain number of tries. Cluster Glue Cluster Glue is a set of libraries, tools, and utilities that are used in the heartbeat and Pacemaker cluster stack. In essence, Cluster Glue is the parts of the cluster stack that do not fit in anywhere else. Basically, it is everything that is not messaging layer and not a resource manager. Resource agents Resource agents are scripts that enable Pacemaker to manage any service that it is unknown to Pacemaker. The agents contain the logic for what to do when the cluster wants to start, stop, or check the health of a service.  A resource agent is an executable file that manages a cluster resource. No formal definition of a cluster resource exists, other than anything that a cluster manages is a resource. Cluster resources can be as diverse as IP addresses, file systems, database services, and entire VMs.  Resource agents run in clustered systems or remotely.  Resource agents can start, stop, or restart services.  Quorum helps ensure that the majority of a cluster agrees on what the resource is. Votequorum is the interface that members use to agree.  Resource agents also provide messaging for applications coordinating or operating across multiple members of a cluster. 2.8.4 Automation with Ansible: Overview Ansible is an open-source automation tool that simplifies IT tasks, which include configuration management, application deployment, and orchestration. You	[-0.069127224,-0.053618584,-0.050542828,-0.020185314,0.09863392,-0.0077970517,-0.020080479,0.008943245,0.033743057,-0.061722763,0.023792276,0.043034542,0.034571543,-0.066252865,0.009518955,-0.025402889,0.06548987,-0.059713613,-0.025929311,-0.0057558664,-0.0383702,-0.010104512,-0.06015476,0.00035142,-0.056492973,0.044966348,-0.063353024,-0.030289756,0.0037820362,0.012917354,0.0507703,0.025582585,0.005431642,0.015524522,0.017057285,0.11832217,0.10052367,-0.039851416,-0.07897557,-0.054849092,0.026761072,-0.11460124,-0.06384987,-0.012794241,0.07730833,-0.026327038,-0.10347967,-0.042978074,0.00029315543,-0.055721745,-0.050747197,-0.07439525,0.014985839,0.03517177,0.05333489,0.066474535,0.04375511,6.9929706e-07,-0.036388114,-0.031691276,0.044959303,-0.036271006,0.009812522,0.050229255,0.07760513,-0.042272154,0.031171834,-0.02184774,0.04258211,-0.04344937,-0.022051694,0.029728139,0.05108109,0.043216124,-0.036769718,0.093610615,-0.027745815,-0.012498499,0.00040835544,0.011168092,-0.04791842,0.05817064,-0.00041283795,0.038539574,-0.005933642,0.03014633,0.023328813,-0.03131334,0.04568392,0.0018091549,-0.015413506,0.07803489,-0.008857494,-0.05515344,0.015021005,-0.027258396,-0.02230705,-0.0026599297,0.030932117,0.055451095,0.0015129027,-0.024744933,0.030985108,-0.019558858,-0.024972389,-0.009030163,-0.08277179,-0.033558123,0.005169923,0.057412174,0.012