462	5	70	52 IBM LinuxONE Resiliency  Transparent and near-continuous application availability from disk failures  Automated and transparent failover and failback GDPS extends the resource sharing, workload balancing, and CA benefits of a parallel environment. It also enhances the capability of an enterprise to recover from disasters and other failures, and to manage planned exception conditions. As a result, you can achieve your own CADR goals. GDPS is a collection of several offerings, each addressing a different set of IT resiliency goals that can be tailored to meet the RPO and RTO for your business. Each GDPS offering uses a combination of system and storage hardware-based or software-based replication and automation, and clustering software technologies:  Metro  Metro HyperSwap Manager  IBM GDPS Virtual Appliance  Extended Disaster Recovery (xDR)  GM  MGM  CA The following sections describe the applicable LinuxONE applicable technologies: Metro, GDPS Virtual Appliance, xDR, GM, and MGM. GDPS Metro A near-CADR solution across two sites that are separated by metropolitan distances. The solution is based on the MM synchronous disk mirroring technology. Provides CADR and production systemsysplex resource management capabilities. Based on the MM synchronous disk mirroring technology, it can achieve an RPO of zero. Typically, the recovery time is less than one hour (RTO  1 hour) after a complete site failure. Metro also supports HyperSwap to provide near-continuous disk availability after a disk failure. GDPS Global Mirror A DR solution across two regions that are separated by virtually unlimited distance. The solution is based on the IBM System Storage GM technology, which is a disk subsystem-based asynchronous form of remote copy. GDPS Metro Global Mirror A 3-site or a symmetrical 4-site configuration is supported:  MGM 3-site A 3-site solution that provides CA across two sites within metropolitan distances in one region and DR to a third site in a second region at virtually unlimited distances. It is based on a combination of the MM and GM technologies.  MGM 4-site A symmetrical 4-site solution that is similar to the 3-site solution in that it provides CA within a region and DR across regions. Also, in the 4-site solution, the two regions are configured symmetrically so that as much CADR protection is provided, no matter which region production runs in.	[-0.04733994,-0.023993151,0.006997819,-0.03458044,-0.0011691543,-0.02817651,-0.014104017,0.10619095,-0.054632943,0.006115094,-0.00096115633,0.03001211,0.093207546,-0.03493378,-0.00041368994,-0.046908896,0.10940182,-0.029707635,0.018148445,-0.019944642,0.007962265,-0.0437606,-0.115330026,-0.03727223,-0.0027717247,-0.0024478978,0.008083758,-0.031708796,-0.038146917,0.012094901,-0.0209114,0.016936006,-0.09155017,0.037963204,0.03311289,0.04906591,0.05317844,-0.0021816872,-0.033605836,-0.16192007,-0.03472301,-0.047639538,-0.05371122,0.014634414,-0.012683677,0.01773789,-0.026699875,-0.003289051,-0.022411969,0.008109681,0.022410097,-0.015808042,0.06621849,0.10411649,0.016199296,0.07054317,0.04941647,0.0042270827,-0.023366008,-0.010664415,0.022375314,-0.05925927,-0.0147874,-0.009224153,0.06175603,0.011775843,0.05512722,0.021636732,-0.031431917,-0.046677746,-0.055154655,-0.018843122,-0.021017177,0.05381162,-0.06340936,0.02151285,0.03688039,-0.0214992,0.042844817,-0.047831576,0.0150636,0.12662885,-0.007888834,0.02239208,-0.020907432,0.006944066,-0.014774541,0.037963003,0.0660349,-0.030787244,0.096800044,0.13105765,0.020702936,-0.023255019,0.013597562,-0.052482918,0.067624874,0.008258944,0.050298378,0.0012280516,0.051182363,0.059411436,0.08722898,-0.03015039,-0.02634723,-0.07647203,-0.024487324,-0.004992546,-0.042253003,0.02637161,-0.0066828746,0.037002817,-0.01079824,-0.049089152,-0.0053679748,-0.028424358,-0.07819657,-0.02018806,0.033468865,-0.031385917,0.008982063,4.140264e-05,0.04189535,-0.06736336,0.05833083,0.046924677,0.0059443065,5.5903738e-33,-0.04525617,0.03353261,-0.07464187,