465	5	73	56 IBM LinuxONE Resiliency To support planned and unplanned outages, these functions are extended to KVM with GDPS 4.5 and later, which provides recovery actions, such as the following examples:  Restart in place of the failing OS images.  Heartbeat checking of Linux guests.  Disk error detection.  Data consistency with freeze functions across zOS and Linux.  Site takeoverfailover of a complete production site.  Single point of control to manage disk mirroring configurations.  Coordinated recovery for planned and unplanned events. More support is available for Linux running as a guest under zVM:  Restart in place of failing OS images.  Order Linux node or cluster startup and shutdown.  Coordinate PHS and UHS of disk subsystems, which are transparent to the OS images and applications that use the disks.  Transparent disk maintenance and failure recovery with HyperSwap across zOS and Linux applications. GDPS MGM GDPS provides DR and production system and sysplex resource management capabilities. Based on GM synchronous disk mirroring technology, it can achieve data loss down to 3 seconds (RPO  3 seconds) and RTO  1 hour. GDPS Global supports two sites that are separated by virtually unlimited distances with minimal impact to user response times. Three-site and four-site configurations are available, such as combining GDPS MM with GM to form GDPS MGM. MGM has the following features:  Down to zero data loss  HyperSwap for disk availability  Protection from regional events  Minimal impact to user response time For more information about GDPS offerings, see IBM GDPS: An Introduction to Concepts and Capabilities, SG24-6374. Table 2-1 shows the capabilities of various GDPS components that are applicable to LinuxONE resiliency scenarios. Table 2-1 GDPS components that are applicable to LinuxONE Feature GDPS Metroa GDPS Virtual Applianceb GDPS GM CA Yes Yes No DR Yes Yes Yes CADR protection against multiple failures Yes No No Max Supported distance 200 KM (fiber) 200 KM (fiber) Virtually unlimited	[-0.032677595,0.015720515,0.007613092,0.007043233,0.078370675,-0.057878047,-0.042714495,0.07616076,-0.037078872,0.039917648,0.032353245,0.06662077,0.057034366,-0.029320823,-0.037967775,-0.04158002,0.079439536,0.006492848,-0.0066568796,-0.00043185876,0.01816028,-0.029503684,-0.03797062,-0.04781017,-0.027492309,-0.03394428,-0.008987015,0.0025117327,-0.016167581,-0.035424203,-0.032318372,0.01624198,-0.05893395,0.03374177,-0.005212274,0.07836162,0.021348359,-0.06555846,-0.0897175,-0.095125794,0.009490382,-0.02562904,-0.07639627,-0.024096973,0.0044080475,0.08798247,0.010707071,-0.036189944,-0.016361125,-0.015169507,-0.0032261787,-0.026554624,0.09694387,0.13825995,0.007848051,0.06594584,0.03184594,-0.046138324,-0.05814796,-0.010749251,0.028269717,-0.02569956,-0.012374264,-0.0062699206,0.08073333,0.074836746,0.08893979,-0.0064677508,-0.04442899,-0.043357417,-0.032224692,0.017271793,0.01276845,0.050914552,-0.09222087,0.024847876,0.001482889,-0.07559974,0.01568056,-0.046404388,0.04868844,0.08227672,0.0021534134,-0.0056000617,0.0024683604,0.041874766,-0.026933618,0.012139022,0.029239826,-0.009419113,0.04224899,0.07325944,0.06942896,-0.0013820949,0.0107888505,0.0014172728,0.054756284,0.0028956214,0.07250803,0.025159273,0.039455537,0.06485374,0.027147554,0.0018038821,0.020189896,0.0047361106,0.017444128,0.032145932,-0.09175437,0.04543538,-0.005787997,0.051372666,0.016656063,-0.044657208,0.02986091,-0.028469937,-0.011734768,0.0217649,-0.04158599,-0.0431454,0.07659377,-0.00032545257,0.043572184,-0.06522692,0.07292002,0.08121205,-0.01279924,7.235312e-33,-0.011194022,-0.0011877756,-0.07001147,-0.07624542,0.021440143,0.028389482,-0.03411588,-0.0006728149,-0.014680025,-0.0011193256,-0.07933584,-0.02404419,0.04374815,-0.10600332,0.024389813,-0.053123366,0.051842473,0.10715067,0.03715845,0.03517253,0.04559971,-0.0409728,0.024420971,-0.045826368,0.068352565,0.030593827,0.000762056,-0.06914526,0.06857572,-0.0077436357,-0.0428434,0.0010787282,-0.07544281,-0