475	5	83	68 IBM LinuxONE Resiliency  Review, plan, and test applications and processes for changes and upgrades to ensure that a rapid failover can be accomplished.  Implement and leverage zVM SSI and zVM Operations Manager. 3.2 Multi-site scenario This scenario introduces one LinuxONE CPC and its associated storage into a second data center, which eliminates the physical site recovery point of failure. This step is necessary on the journey to high availability and disaster recovery (HADR). 3.2.1 Multi-site scenario details In the multi-site scenario, the examples that follow use the following components:  Two physical sites at metro distance (up to 300 km with DS8870 Metro Mirror (MM))  One or more LinuxONE systems per site  Two or more Storage Systems per site with synchronous replication:  Local or between sites replication  zVM as hypervisor, and ECKD disks on both sites with HyperPAV The multi-site resiliency scenario is basically the flexible site scenario with components that are replicated to a secondary site. Figure 3-5 on page 69 shows the 2-site basic components and Storage Systems data that is replicated synchronously between the sites.	[-0.05196943,-0.046812773,-0.06731842,-0.008079547,0.030545408,-0.060258526,-0.05562439,0.06799399,-0.092785105,-0.018412547,0.031925783,0.05118641,0.10387171,-0.05611394,0.04824236,-0.00275347,0.09224904,-0.023187622,-0.0115048485,0.06708448,0.047068313,-0.07187296,-0.028714446,-0.042285718,-0.0007436968,0.018383494,-0.041522264,0.05643609,0.007079775,-0.035323672,0.028265836,0.027358962,-0.09259831,0.03184701,0.026300933,0.045755878,0.024924992,-0.0658671,-0.03714329,-0.06678672,0.017058881,-0.0055769533,-0.08043863,0.009873018,0.019607902,0.034291882,0.014449651,-0.013944658,-0.018695816,-0.07149902,0.026365098,-0.041807834,0.056611978,0.1176974,-0.054426737,0.04447066,0.06989247,-0.0054209093,-0.023177342,0.0074341744,0.09106761,-0.007927152,0.037340775,0.0010996793,0.07900185,-0.019434812,0.080064796,0.004370645,-0.0