477	5	85	-Active) deployment on page 58. Hot-Cold (Active-Passive) configuration In a Hot-Cold configuration, the secondary (DR) site can be a dark or dormant site that is ready to be used if the primary site fails. Data is replicated between the sites. The workload is not split, and each site is configured to handle all operations. Manual intervention is normally required to activate extra resources and the partitions at the cold (passive site). Therefore, the cold environment, which is often used in a DR situation, needs more time to activate.	[0.0038805176,-0.06466966,0.015789622,0.07335194,0.045360126,-0.079170614,-0.023325166,0.021575736,-0.03343213,0.043325447,0.060195778,0.0585224,0.06342385,0.011788743,0.07744318,-0.0139475055,0.009486027,-0.08088997,-0.03130874,0.0064865127,-0.0027870438,0.028684646,-0.10644002,-0.00949937,-0.030536516,0.025589248,-0.07488083,0.05773397,-0.0074498663,-0.014519194,-0.018981053,0.07564276,-0.0036108943,0.0064331917,0.074935146,0.021564769,-0.05162884,-0.0057971505,-0.05266093,0.015286271,0.048780914,-0.08185551,0.023310281,0.045696676,-0.026358346,0.00077704794,-0.07496752,-0.019511571,0.024060888,-0.088184685,0.009592282,-0.05410045,-0.0018151859,0.11726372,-0.09167971,0.059917185,0.054742526,-0.083398305,-0.014699385,-0.058469504,0.067494705,0.0427034,-0.0610755,0.037221406,0.11301876,-0.060362205,0.066833995,-0.074011564,0.09639022,-0.07327457,-0.022222161,0.06247566,-0.007980312,-0.0775744,0.075787716,-0.061789736,0.0039800545,0.006113296,0.085002154,-0.088699706,0.07395297,-0.04196129,0.021248754,0.030189147,-0.05200851,-0.03694232,0.021485684,-0.0491764,0.0067977305,0.00068414636,0.04510419,0.01570215,0.06441567,0.02748381,-0.09209724,0.034922525,0.003823943,0.06114091,-0.025133215,-0.017702479,0.0070154555,-0.081504755,-0.0019120285,0.018657926,-0.021056063,-0.1035416,8.805788e-05,-0.036670752,0.036665488,-0.04309937,-0.025982551,0.04830993,0.03322748,-0.046758164,0.007676135,0.047653202,-0.004431259,-0.015342155,0.048