497	5	105	94 IBM LinuxONE Resiliency Case 5: A zVM virtual network encounters a problem Table 4-5 describes a case where a zVM virtual network encounters a problem. Table 4-5 Case 5: A zVM virtual network encounters a problem Figure 4-10 zVM network, IO, or SSI problem Failing component What happens Mitigation, workaround, or recovery A zVM virtual network encounters a problem. See Figure 4-10. Traffic for zVM or guests is disrupted, which leads to problems with heartbeats and system assessment. There is disruption to the client workload.  Use link aggregation to collect multiple OSA ports into a common logical channel.  Set up VSWITCH automatic failover (four controller nodes) in case of a disrupted network operation.  Use an Inter-VSWITCH Link to coordinate multiple zVM systems. Impact: Negligible. Link aggregation collates resources, and failover prevents an outage. Time to recovery of the failing component: If it is physical networking, the time to recover varies. If it is virtual networking, expect 1 - 2 hours to debug and rebuild. CoreOS (not RHEL) Operations Manager for VM xDR Proxy RedHat OCP xDR Proxy OCP Control Node (control plane) OCP Compute Node zVM V7.3 with SSI Logical Partition (PRSM) DS8K (ECKD) DS8K (ECKD) LinuxONE Emperor 4 hardware	[-0.0152889555,-0.016658064,0.006552561,0.03544687,0.033715136,-0.008270452,-0.045690604,0.08472839,-0.06369198,-0.0014393985,0.0036709572,0.032826338,0.06123631,-0.027064014,0.020795554,0.092879474,0.082218975,6.364244e-05,-0.05238223,0.04757536,0.020208567,0.003882672,-0.022651792,-0.0558515,-0.017194023,-0.052283138,-0.02447088,0.032955103,-0.025049215,-0.02321471,-0.020073669,0.060524385,-0.110439,0.0072730184,0.0038452921,0.03914798,0.029212669,-0.028678806,-0.035016492,-0.041573487,0.014352451,0.014940267,-0.052038122,-0.035085164,-0.0034194244,0.007209406,0.0016110012,-0.039630637,0.015812833,-0.031988848,-0.0058957213,-0.016330328,0.091381535,0.13704093,0.028215889,0.03413032,-0.02077529,0.0015368691,-0.041827