498	5	106	96 IBM LinuxONE Resiliency Case 8: zVM SSI takes a hit to its Persistent Data Record Table 4-8 describes a case where a zVM SSI takes a hit to its Persistent Data Record. Table 4-8 Case 8: zVM SSI takes a hit to its Persistent Data Record Figure 4-11 SSI Persistent Data Record takes a hit Failing component What happens Mitigation, workaround, or recovery A zVM SSI takes a hit to its Persistent Data Record. See Figure 4-11 The Persistent Data Record volume maintains the state of the overall cluster and heartbeat tracking. If the cluster is damaged, the whole cluster moves into recovery mode. Regarding GDPS, the PDR is not handled separately from the rest of the GDPS consistency group. Impact: Minimal. HyperSwap takes 2 - 3 seconds. Persistent Data Record becomes a single point of failure (SPOF) until the original Persistent Data Record volume is restored. Time to recovery of the failing component: After the storage device is repaired (see Case 1: Storage unit failure on page 90), MM resumes active backup. CoreOS (not RHEL) Operations Manager for VM xDR Proxy RedHat OCP xDR Proxy OCP Control Node (control plane) OCP Compute Node zVM V7.3 with SSI Logical Partition (PRSM) DS8K (ECKD) DS8K (ECKD) LinuxONE Emperor 4 hardware	[-0.09180486,0.0065449206,-0.02330349,0.032615725,0.074905045,-0.040498484,-0.045931593,0.020347254,-0.01923639,-0.062370725,0.06390158,0.079811774,0.09509973,-0.034247443,-0.026999516,-0.00421278,0.034631383,-0.03886293,-0.034659196,0.06478919,-0.01626585,0.04977384,-0.0531846,-0.030980863,-0.016247304,0.008435094,0.0013085247,-4.229818e-06,0.017889298,0.023206348,-0.006549311,0.029381115,-0.07485504,0.08312633,-0.010721803,0.030530855,0.06056099,0.010626655,-0.05868908,-0.051722374,0.026480934,-0.043664236,-0.078570545,-0.035088662,-0.0012455583,0.0620227,-0.0019467394,-0.057395194,-0.07050679,-0.015898945,-0.072726354,0.032272596,0.08390508,0.15474986,-0.016184673,0.07656018,0.0058337455,0.04151384,-0.037330855,-0.007998415,-0.0041408837