503	5	111	106 IBM LinuxONE Resiliency Case 4: Planned outage for GDPS xDR Table 4-19 describes a case where there is a planned outage for GDPS xDR. Table 4-19 Case 4: Planned outage for GDPS xDR 4.4 Disaster recovery This section describes disaster scenarios, such as the loss of entire data center or regions due to natural disasters, power outages, or human-generated catastrophes; and other events that can cause availability loss. Generally, physical data centers (and their full recovery) are measured at five 9s of availability (99.999).  Data center providers have service-level agreements (SLAs) regarding availability and resources.  Calculating availability, which is based on data centers worldwide, is less reliable than for hardware or software.  Standards vary in adoption and locality, for example, ANSOBICSI 002-2019.  Use a tiered approach based on how much a client can tolerate (or afford). For less extreme problems (water, electricity, or air conditioning outages), data centers should provide duplication of resource, and have backup generators, alternative lines, and disparate power grids (for maintenance and planned outages). The rate of failure should be low, but depending on the nature of the disaster, restoring the physical assets might be difficult or impossible. Having geographically dispersed data centers minimizes the chance of a single disaster hitting both data centers simultaneously. Having data replication through GDPS is important whether the presented framework is configured Active-Active. Failing component What happens Mitigation, workaround, or recovery There is a planned outage for Red Hat OpenShift Container Platform. See Figure 4-17 on page 104. NA.  There is no outage.  xDR proxies can be recycled one at a time after maintenance. The system is never without a local agent.  Similarly, multiple zOS K-systems update one at a time, but never without GDPS xDR. There is a recovery error on GDPS xDR. There are problems with storage synchronization, and there is a lack of failover support until the problem is mitigated.  Recycle or restart.  No known cases of this situation occurring.	[-0.041502737,-0.0642988,0.0077889557,0.0146792,0.041458145,-0.017875196,-0.04626079,0.118226886,-0.024304768,0.0009942167,0.009234618,0.041878156,0.07460133,-0.06846726,0.03359476,0.013338568,0.050215025,-0.0637129,-0.084535174,-0.012839549,-0.0010512066,-0.019490063,-0.10752953,-0.028296417,0.032783955,0.031221967,0.016939264,-0.005207448,-0.044836544,0.049307507,-0.037929945,0.010661151,-0.046818182,0.025394034,0.052750792,0.064674474,0.051341277,-0.028508462,0.0036318458,-0.028831031,-0.012463768,-0.049573135,-0.062031277,0.00599997,-0.026797824,0.0059616775,-0.042512417,-0.021651499,-0.055228453,0.044157386,0.08150231,0.04347353,0.05726415,0.109167606,0.01883841,0.022801064,0.006659834,-0.04481847,-0.032372095,0.040962886,0.04572277,-0.03520028,-0.020405937,0.0010564197,0.040838167,0.037373245,0.07446158,-0.003044721,-0.025553066,0.024044866,-0.06783464,-0.035313062,-0.00852223,0.04051969,-0.069791585,0.018568866,0.081173785,-0.012674744,0.076457635,0.00903039,0.036780797,0.11584755,-0.02440073,0.027373277,-0.030999329,-0.034426514,0.030923864,0.04674483,0.032297738,-0.0011649632,0.03575431,0.087333255,0.09872871,0.00068631704,0.025758782,-0.00585074,0.01498803,-0.06936151,0.037798677,-0.019765018,0.04242438,0.04383361,0.07589064,-0.047065202,0.017528288,-0.09193446,-0.017360244,-0.006538547,-0.032256033,0.05173956,-0.052649405,-0.00414454,0.026545523,-0.07128386,0.022769671,-0.017101247,-0.07060048,-0.008045688,-0.008614166,-0.045616936,0.015628638,0.00899284,0.071940444,-0.0782615,0.051501438,0.035533685,-0.004722826,4.5603087e-33,-0.065352805,0.009525979,-0.018097242,-0.07494879,-0.007977137,-0.040304087,-0.03298556,0.014266365,0.0117828185,0.0022742145,-0.0459172,-0.00071211753,-0.018193468,-0.08773038,0.09036907,0.018773751,0.111552656,0.079417385,0.09195473,0.026049383,0.04215548,-0.06761928,0.07247665,0.0024138691,0